                            <comment id="315103" author="adilger" created="Sat, 9 Oct 2021 06:04:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed via &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11104&quot; title=&quot;rename under striped directory may cause deadlock&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11104&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11104&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="81662" author="di.wang" created="Tue, 15 Apr 2014 18:22:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;oh, not critical, probably not serious enough to become a blocker. I just found this issue, when I inspect #9538, I guess it might cause some security issue, since we use the attr to do permission check here. But the fix should be easy IMHO, just add another attr_get before call mdd_parent_fid.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="81657" author="adilger" created="Tue, 15 Apr 2014 18:18:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Di, how critical is this issue?  Does it need to be a blocker for 2.6.0?  Does it mean the remote directories are not working correctly?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
